Yunnan:Coordinating and standardizing rural public welfare post management-Xinhuanet Xinhua Agency, Kunming, December 12 th(Reporter Lin Bifeng) In order to continue to provide employment assistance to the poverty-stricken population and consolidate and expand the key achievements in poverty alleviation, Yunnan Province has recently issued relevant policies to promote the management of rural public welfare posts to help promote rural revitalization in an all-round way. According to the relevant person in charge of the Yunnan Provincial Department of Human Resources and Social Security, at present, Yunnan has developed 448,300 rural public welfare posts to resettle the poverty-stricken labor force and other rural disadvantaged groups for employment, helping the poverty-stricken people to increase their employment income and consolidate the key achievements in poverty alleviation.It plays an important role in effectively improving various public service capabilities in rural areas. The new regulations were jointly issued by seven departments, including Yunnan People 's Association, Rural Revitalization and Finance. They mainly standardize the scope of targets, fund management, post development and post management for grass-roots recruitment of rural public welfare personnel. In terms of post development and setting, the new regulations are clear, in accordance with "setting posts according to needs, determining people according to posts, dynamic management and total amount control","who develops, who uses,Who is responsible for "and" one person, one post, voluntary disclosure, unified management "principle. Recruitment procedures must be in accordance with the announcement, declaration, review, publicity, employment, pre-job training and arrangement of posts and other steps. In addition, the new regulations also clarify the specific responsibilities of the main development departments of rural public welfare posts, the subsidy standards and subsidy methods of rural public welfare posts, and stipulate that the development departments of rural public welfare posts should purchase accidental injury commercial insurance for rural public welfare post resettlement personnel;Require relevant departments to regularly supervise the payment of subsidies for rural public welfare posts.
